Safaricom of Kenya Rises on Speculation Profit Will Increase

-- B y   E r i c   O m b o k
-- 
2011-03-28T09:25:27Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-28/safaricom-of-kenya-rises-on-speculation-profit-will-increase.html
Safaricom Ltd. (SAFCOM) ,  Kenya ’s biggest
mobile-network operator, gained for the first day in three on
speculation earnings in the year through March will increase.  The stock of Kenya’s largest company by market value
climbed as much as 2.5 percent to 4.05 shillings before trading
5 cents, or 1.3 percent, higher at 4 shillings by 11:23 a.m. in
Nairobi.  “We are approaching the year-end on March 31,” Eric Musau, an analyst at Nairobi-based African Alliance Securities
Kenya Ltd., said by phone today. “We are estimating a small
increase in profitability, despite all the challenges.”  Earnings per share are estimated to rise 8.6 percent, Musau
said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Eric Ombok in Nairobi at 
 eombok@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
